<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="554" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,402,1041]" pageId="16" pageNumber="554">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,260,403,429]" pageId="16" pageNumber="554">Remarks</emphasis>
. This species was only known from “ 
<collectingCountry box="[675,843,403,429]" name="Colombia" pageId="16" pageNumber="554">Nova Granada</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[853,937,403,429]" country="Colombia" name="Bogota" pageId="16" pageNumber="554">Bogota</collectingRegion>
” (
<bibRefCitation author="Stal, C." box="[961,1072,402,429]" pageId="16" pageNumber="554" pagination="1 - 159" refId="ref16712" refString="Stal, C. (1872) Enumeratio Hemipterorum. Bidrag till en forteckning ofver alla hittills kanda Hemiptera, jemte systematiska meddelanden. 2. Kongliga Svenska Vetenskaps-Akademiens Handlingar, 10, 1 - 159. https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / part / 147036" type="journal article" year="1872">Stål 1872</bibRefCitation>
), a political division that encompassed mostly what is nowadays 
<collectingCountry box="[522,632,439,465]" name="Colombia" pageId="16" pageNumber="554">Colombia</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[687,779,439,465]" name="Panama" pageId="16" pageNumber="554">Panama</collectingCountry>
. This is the first time that an exact locality is given for this species. Unlike other 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1807" box="[402,530,475,501]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="554" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Reduviidae</taxonomicName>
specimens similarly labelled as “Bogotá” that might be actually from lowland areas (e.g., 
<bibRefCitation author="Forero, D." box="[283,427,511,538]" pageId="16" pageNumber="554" pagination="1 - 47" refId="ref15285" refString="Forero, D. (2006) New records of Reduviidae (Hemiptera: Heteroptera) from Colombia and other Neotropical countries. Zootaxa, 1107 (1), 1 - 47. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 1107.1.1" type="journal article" year="2006">Forero 2006</bibRefCitation>
), the examined specimen and photograph of the 
<typeStatus box="[985,1072,511,537]" pageId="16" pageNumber="554">syntype</typeStatus>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Holston, K." box="[1088,1246,511,537]" pageId="16" pageNumber="554" refId="ref15757" refString="Holston, K. (2019). Entomological Collections (NHRS), Swedish Museum of Natural History (NRM). Version 26.636. Swedish Museum of Natural History. Occurrence dataset. Available from: https: // www. gbif. org / (accessed 15 September 2019) https: // doi. org / 10.15468 / fpzyjx" type="url" year="2019">Holston 2019</bibRefCitation>
) indicate that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1872" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Castolus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="554" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="multicinctus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="554">C. multicinctus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is found in the high Andes, and only known from the Bogotá plateau. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1872" box="[1097,1327,547,573]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Castolus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="554" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="multicintus">
<emphasis box="[1097,1327,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="554">Castolus multicintus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
might be confused with species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hahn" authorityYear="1834" box="[429,557,583,609]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Rhynocoris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="554" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[429,557,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="554">Rhynocoris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
due to its external resemblance, but 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hahn" authorityYear="1834" box="[959,1087,583,609]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Rhynocoris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="554" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[959,1087,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="554">Rhynocoris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
do not occur in South America. 
<bibRefCitation author="Maldonado, J." box="[151,360,619,646]" pageId="16" pageNumber="554" pagination="435 - 446" refId="ref15942" refString="Maldonado, J. (1976) Three new species of Castolus and a key to the species (Hemiptera: Reduviidae). Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington, 78, 435 - 446. https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / part / 56099" type="journal article" year="1976">Maldonado (1976)</bibRefCitation>
redescribed this species based on a single female 
<typeStatus box="[919,1006,619,645]" pageId="16" pageNumber="554">syntype</typeStatus>
specimen. Label data of the examined specimen indicate that it was on a “fique”, probably a 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ventenat" authorityYear="1793" box="[762,867,655,680]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Furcraea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="16" pageNumber="554" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[762,867,655,680]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="554">Furcraea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName authorityName="de Jussieu" authorityYear="1789" box="[882,1044,655,681]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="16" pageNumber="554" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Asparagaceae</taxonomicName>
), preying on a caterpillar. Males of this species are so far unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="554" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,402,1041]" pageId="16" pageNumber="554">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,726,752]" pageId="16" pageNumber="554">Distribution</emphasis>
. Originally described from “ 
<collectingCountry box="[675,845,727,753]" name="Colombia" pageId="16" pageNumber="554">Nova Granada</collectingCountry>
” (
<bibRefCitation author="Stal, C." box="[872,986,726,753]" pageId="16" pageNumber="554" pagination="1 - 159" refId="ref16712" refString="Stal, C. (1872) Enumeratio Hemipterorum. Bidrag till en forteckning ofver alla hittills kanda Hemiptera, jemte systematiska meddelanden. 2. Kongliga Svenska Vetenskaps-Akademiens Handlingar, 10, 1 - 159. https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / part / 147036" type="journal article" year="1872">Stål 1872</bibRefCitation>
), and here recorded from two localities nearby 
<collectingRegion box="[234,318,763,789]" country="Colombia" name="Bogota" pageId="16" pageNumber="554">Bogotá</collectingRegion>
, on the high Andes in 
<collectingCountry box="[568,678,763,789]" name="Colombia" pageId="16" pageNumber="554">Colombia</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation box="[694,798,763,789]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1556,1580]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,777,1533]" captionTargetId="figure-210@19.[151,1435,777,1533]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 10. Distribution map of Castolus species based on data from examined specimens and iNaturalist observations. A. C. multicintus Stål, 1872; B. C. pallidus Maldonado, 1976; C. C. plagiaticollis Stål, 1858; D. C. rufomarginatus Champion, 1899." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5556798" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5556798/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="554">Fig. 10A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
